cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the use of business analytics and data mining approaches for terminal planning and management in container terminals. This involves the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which fall under the category of cs.AI and cs.LG. The paper also discusses the use of data to identify and understand causes of inefficiencies and disruptions, which falls under the category of cs.CY (cybersecurity). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of data within and around container terminals, which may require the use of cryptographic techniques to secure the data, falling under the category of cs.CR (cryptography) and cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing).
